    <div class="full-title with-title-branding">
      <div class="title-branding"><a href="/taxonomy/term/868"><img src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/sight-and-sound-logo-280x69.png?itok=AEegRSbk" alt="" /></a></div>
  
  <h1>
          Critics’ 50 Greatest Documentaries of All Time    
    
      </h1>

  
  
        <div class="copy">
              <div class="intro"><p>What are the greatest documentaries ever made? We polled 340 critics, programmers and filmmakers in the search for authoritative answers. Nick James introduces our poll while, below, we list the critics’ top 56 documentaries.</p>
<p>Across the page, you can see the <a href="/sight-sound-magazine/filmmakers-greatest-docs">filmmakers’ top 35 films</a>, or now browse all the votes and comments on our <a href="http://www.bfi.org.uk/sight-sound-magazine/greatest-docs-full-poll">dedicated interactive webpage</a>. Further features and reflections on our poll can be found in our <a href="/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/september-2014-issue">September 2014 issue</a>.</p>
</div>
            
      
              <p class="author-data">
          <span class="author"> Sight & Sound  contributors  , <a href="/people/brian-winston"> Brian  Winston  </a>, <a href="/people/jonathan-rosenbaum"> Jonathan  Rosenbaum  </a>, <a href="/people/adam-nayman"> Adam   Nayman  </a>,  Philip  French  ,  Nicolas  Rapold  ,  Rachael  Rakes  </span><br /><span class="date">Updated: <time datetime="2019-04-25">25 April 2019</time></span>        </p>
      
      
          </div>
  </div>
  </div>
</div>
